trend_summary: Imagery shows a largely wooded peninsula gradually converted to agriculture. Early frames are dominated by dense forest with scattered clearings; successive scenes reveal expanding rectangular fields, thinner riparian belts and a slightly denser road web. Built-up footprints remain tiny, so the landscape evolves from forested to farm-mosaic while staying sparsely settled.
notable_changes: Marked reduction of continuous forest cover, especially in the north-east and south-east quadrants.
Appearance and enlargement of rectangular cropland parcels along the eastern shoreline and interior valleys.
Growth of an unpaved road lattice connecting new clearings and fields.
Riparian vegetation thinning, exposing more river and creek banks.
Scattered new farmsteads or outbuildings near central road junctions.
